BC Reference Model Version 1.0.0
oncology

Element StageTimingPrefix

Documentation:
Indicates when the staging was done, in terms of treatment landmarks, either clinical (at diagnosis prior to treatment) (c), pathologic (post-surgical) (p), post-neoadjuvant clinical (yc), or post-neoadjuvant pathologic(yp). The stage timing code is prefixed on the N stage. For example, for post-neoadjuvant clinical staging, the N categories are preceded by 'yc' (e.g. ycNX)
